      <section id="details">
        <h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--mobile-top-margin  ">Details</h2>


        
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<h3 id="uk-financial-sanctions-general-guidance">UK financial sanctions: general guidance</h3>
<p><a rel="external" href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2018/13/contents" class="govuk-link">The Sanctions and Anti-Money Laundering Act 2018 (the Sanctions Act)</a> will enable sanctions to continue uninterrupted after 11pm on 31 December 2020. Secondary legislation under the Sanctions Act, in the form of Statutory Instruments (SIs), will transfer existing EU sanctions into UK law.</p>

<p>During the transition period, the government can also bring into force autonomous UK sanctions regimes under the Sanctions Act. However, most sanctions regimes, for which regulations have been laid under the Sanctions Act, will not come into force fully until 11pm on 31 December 2020.</p>

<p>To facilitate implementation, <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/uk-sanctions-regimes-under-the-sanctions-act" class="govuk-link">FCO has published statutory guidance</a> on these regimes. OFSI has also published updated general guidance on financial sanctions for information purposes.This guidance  will only become operational when SIs under the Sanctions Act come into force. This is therefore for information only.</p>

<h3 id="russia-financial-sanctions-guidance">Russia financial sanctions guidance</h3>
<p>OFSI has also published specific guidance in respect of the financial and investment restrictions in the Russia financial sanctions regime. This guidance does not currently apply and would only come into effect at 11pm on 31 December 2020, or when the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/uk-sanctions-on-russia" class="govuk-link">Russia (Sanctions) (EU Exit) Regulations 2019</a> come into force. This is therefore for information only at this stage.</p>

</div>
</div>

      </section>
